As a decent but not yet highly skilled solver, I tend to agree. Over the last five years, I'm finding some - certainly not all - of the Thursday - Saturday puzzles more doable than earlier. I'm sure some of that is just me getting better at it, but although my ego fights the concept, objectively I have to acknowledge that part of it is that these "second half of the week" puzzles aren't quite as challenging as they used to be. If I'm able to do more of these puzzles than I used to, and in significantly faster times, that doesn't speak well for their difficulty -- realistically, I shouldn't be able to complete many of them yet. 

Now, in defense of the NYT, I'm betting that a lot of people subscribe primarily for the puzzles, and in this age of declining readership and trending away from traditional newspapers, they have to keep the majority of those "I'm here for the games" subscribers happy -- even if that means disappointing the small minority of "elite" solvers.

