I often get orders for eggs "over well," although it's more commonly worded "over hard." Not as often as "over easy" or "over medium" (my personal choice.) Trick is to cook the eggs until the the yolk is entirely set, without scorching the whites. Also, if you're going to order a egg "over anything," it's assumed it's going to be fried, and saying so is redundant.

